---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
import Markdown from '../../../Markdown.astro';
import AIBalloon from '../../AIBalloon.astro';
import AIBalloonMessage from '../../AIBalloonMessage.astro';
import AIResponseMessage from '../../AIResponseMessage.astro';
import HighlightBox from '../../HighlightBox.astro';
import HighlightInline from '../../HighlightInline.astro';
import HighlightInlineItem from '../../HighlightInlineItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Set Expectations Over Time, Not Just Once"
  description="Reinforce what the AI can do and what the user's role is at key moments—not only on first use. Remind when context changes or when the stakes are high."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={496} label="Expectations over time" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>
          I’d like to create a lawn using Phyla nodiflora. How can I do it?
        </AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <Markdown
          typography="detail"
          content={`
You can start by preparing the soil well (removing weeds, loosening the ground, and ensuring good drainage), then planting Phyla plugs or cuttings spaced about 20-30 cm apart.
`}
        />
        <mds-text typography="detail">
          <HighlightInline>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="expectations over time" variant="info">
              Regular watering in the first weeks is important to help them establish. In the first
              1-2 months, you’ll mainly see the plants taking root, with limited horizontal growth.
              Between 3-6 months, they should begin spreading and covering the soil more
              consistently, depending on temperature and care.<br />
            </HighlightInlineItem>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="warns that will takes time" variant="warning">
              Keep in mind that full coverage can take a full growing season or more.
            </HighlightInlineItem>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="Prepare for possible failures" variant="warning">
              You may need to manage weeds and fill any gaps where plants don’t establish properly.<br
              />
            </HighlightInlineItem>
            <HighlightInlineItem label="Aligns to expectations" variant="success">
              Once established, maintenance is much lower compared to traditional grass.
            </HighlightInlineItem>
          </HighlightInline>
        </mds-text>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>
          I’d like to create a lawn using Phyla nodiflora. How can I do it?
        </AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="vague and elusive effort" variant="error">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
Plant Phyla nodiflora evenly across your garden and water it regularly. It will quickly form a dense, uniform lawn with minimal effort.
`}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Repeat or reinforce scope, reliability, and user role at important moments (e.g. before send,
      before high-stakes use).
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Rely only on first-use or one-time messaging; assume users will remember.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      When the context becomes higher-stakes (e.g. legal, external audience), restate limitations
      and user responsibility.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Treat every interaction the same; avoid reminding when the cost of misunderstanding is high.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
